    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource leak in rrc_find_ue_index function\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_find_ue_index` function in `openair2/RRC/LTE/utils.c` was incomplete, containing only a comment block and no actual implementation. This caused issues downstream where the function was expected to properly search for UE context based on L2 ID.\n\nThis fix implements the missing functionality and adds proper resource handling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/utils.c`: Implemented the incomplete `rrc_find_ue_index` function to properly search for UE index based on MAC ID\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/utils.c`: Added missing `<string.h>` include for `bcmp` function\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, calling `rrc_find_ue_index` would result in undefined behavior as the function had no implementation. This could cause segmentation faults or incorrect UE context handling in RRC procedures.\n\nThe function now properly searches through the `CH_rrc_inst[Mod_id].Info.UE_info` array comparing L2 IDs and returns either the matching index or 0xffff on failure to find a match.\n"
}